<span class="block h6 bold mt-1">Quotes</span>
For quotes, there are inline quotes, which are implemented by utilizing the <span><code class="hljs"><span class="language-xml"><span class="hljs-tag">&lt;<span class="hljs-name">q</span>&gt;</span>
</span></code></span> element or by using the class <span><code class="hljs"><span class="hljs-selector-class">.quote</span>
</code></span>, and there are block quotes, which are implemented by using the <span><code class="hljs"><span class="hljs-selector-class">.blockquote</span></code></span> class or the 
<span><code class="hljs"><span class="language-xml"><span class="hljs-tag">&lt;<span class="hljs-name">blockquote</span>&gt;</span></span></code></span> element.
The blockquote takes up its own line(s), and the quote is an inline element.
<span class="block h6 bold mt-1">Asides</span>
Asides are surfaces which should be the direct child of a block element and that only take up a portion of the width of the screen.
Asides are implemented by using the <span><code class="hljs"><span class="language-xml"><span class="hljs-tag">&lt;<span class="hljs-name">aside</span>&gt;</span></span></code></span> element, and 
they only take up a certain percentage of the width of their parent block element. Aside elements can have a 
<span><code class="hljs"><span class="hljs-selector-class">.left</span></code></span> or <span><code class="hljs"><span class="hljs-selector-class">.right</span></code></span> class which controls which way they float.
<div class="alert warning outlined small icon mt-1" role="alert">
<svg focusable="false" inert viewBox="0 0 24 24" tabindex="-1" title="Details"><path d="M12 3 2 21h20L12 3zm1 5.92L18.6 19H13V8.92zm-2 0V19H5.4L11 8.92z"></path></svg>
<p class="alert">
